  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I forget a person whom I loved for 6 years?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're going through this. Healing from a long-term relationship can be challenging, but there are steps you can take to help yourself move forward:\n\n1. **Allow Yourself to Grieve:** It's natural to feel a range of emotions\u2014sadness, anger, confusion. Give yourself permission to experience these feelings without judgment.\n\n2. **Seek Support:** Reach out to friends, family members, or a therapist. Talking about your feelings can provide relief and offer new perspectives.\n\n3. **Establish a Routine:** Creating a daily schedule can provide structure and a sense of normalcy. Include activities that you enjoy and that make you feel good.\n\n4. **Engage in Self-Care:** Focus on taking care of your physical and mental health. This can include exercising, eating well, getting enough sleep, and practicing relaxation techniques like meditation or deep breathing.\n\n5. **Pursue New Interests:** Exploring new hobbies or interests can help redirect your focus and provide opportunities to meet new people.\n\n6. **Limit Contact if Needed:** If possible, take a break from communicating with the person to give yourself space to heal. This might include unfollowing them on social media or avoiding places you used to frequent together.\n\n7. **Reflect on the Relationship:** Take time to understand what you've learned from the relationship and how you've grown. This can help you gain clarity and prepare for future relationships.\n\n8. **Be Patient with Yourself:** Healing takes time, and it's okay to have good days and bad days. Don't rush the process or set strict timelines for yourself.\n\n9. **Consider Professional Help:** If you're finding it particularly difficult to cope, a mental health professional can provide strategies and support tailored to your situation.\n\nRemember, it's okay to seek help and take the time you need to heal. Surround yourself with supportive people and be kind to yourself during this difficult time.",
